data.description: Charming Cutten Craftsman tucked in to a ¼ acre lot backing up to a greenbelt  with close access to forested trails for hiking. Built in 2004, this 4 bedroom 2.5 bath 2,090 square foot home has a split level floorplan with the kitchen being upstairs, looking out to the deck and garden area below. The kitchen opens up to the large living room, with breakfast bar and pantry, soaked in natural light, with an extra bonus room, complete with gas fire place that could be an extra bedroom or office space. The primary bedroom is extra large with a walk in closet, located upstairs as well, with soaking tub in the primary bathroom highlighted by a skylight. Three more oversized bedrooms downstairs with lots of extra storage and laundry. Finished two car garage and solar panels for low energy bills!
